        ]
      },
      "date": "2012-10-17 08:30:36.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Verified\n\nTests received by maloo, run on CentOS release 6.3/x86_64, CentOS release 5.8/x86_64: (https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sessions/272e3e62-1831-11e2-beb7-52540035b04c).  Ran 12 tests.  No failures.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "a05269353a2ad3daf8c019ba98b3489e226cbf9c",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2012-10-17 08:41:55.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nAlex, do you think this is worthwhile to land, or just to keep for debugging?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "25e479529597ec992e6244342461e6c30ebd87d6",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bzzz"
      },
      "date": "2012-10-17 09:35:11.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve\n\n",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "d8aecf5f8a6ce1dcac1f2db0fb84e59226474746",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bzzz"
      },
      "date": "2012-10-17 09:36:42.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI'd land it to involve more people. I'd even suggest to LBUG() in case of overflow, given this isn't a production branch.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "3155ca25b9998739fa34ca034ad4195958278117",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2012-10-17 09:39:34.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nNo, I don't want to LBUG() just because of this.  That would make local node testing almost impossible, and since the journal credits are much to pessimistic in many cases (e.g. accounting superblock multiple times, more group blocks than exist, etc) I don't think it is warranted.  If we had \"perfect\" accounting of our compound transactions, then I would feel better about adding an LBUG(), but not today.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "284b4545339b4a0e6ca7a127e696d95ae14020cc",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bzzz"
      },
      "date": "2012-10-17 09:42:23.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nwell, I'm OK with leaving messages only. that suggestion was to learn quickly where this happen now.\n\nbtw, with ofd precreation fixed I don't get this warning anymore (though it might be  I missed that). \n\ngoing to try with LBUG() locally..",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "28cb6650f72c32c00d74d515b51a351d30f17ad8",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 118,
        "name": "Mikhail Pershin",
        "email": "mpershin@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "tappro"
      },
      "date": "2012-10-22 13:48:44.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve\n\n",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
